description.narrative: Data generation, analysis and use was put at the heart of Unicef WCARO strategy on nutrition, allowing for generation of evidences on prevention and treatment of all forms of under-nutrition in different contexts and to influence policies, strategies and interventions. As a result, countries have higher knowledge and skills to address gaps in data availability, can perform stronger analysis to better advise leaders and decision makers. Attention to unstable contexts, such as humanitarian emergencies, was improved thanks to robust information system and release of monthly bulletins providing latest developments. The monitoring of KRC2 implementation has improved. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:17/01/2020
